stretchRows(25.10)                                          stretchRows(25.10)

Name
       stretchRows - Stretches selected rows

Syntax
        stretchRows

       [-help]

       {-left | -right | -left -right}

       [-toCoreEdge]

       Stretches selected rows. You can use this command after importing a de-
       sign.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each stretchRows parameter. For a  detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man stretchRows

       -left  Specifies that the left edge of  all  selected  rows  should  be
              aligned to the left-most edge among all selected rows.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -right Specifies  that  the  right  edge of all selected rows should be
              aligned to the right-most edge among all selected rows.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -toCoreEdge
              Specifies that row edges should be aligned to the core boundary.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       The following command specifies that the left edge of all selected rows
       should be aligned to the left-most edge among all selected rows.

       stretchRows -left

